---
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="about me | hihorton"
	description="Operations professional turned aspiring cloud engineer, documenting the journey."
	pubDate={new Date('March 10 2026')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<p>
		I'm Michael Horton, an operations professional turned aspiring cloud engineer, currently
		building the skills and credentials to make that transition official.
	</p>

	<p>
		By day I'm a Team Leader at FedEx Express, working in aircraft operations where I manage
		people, processes, and logistics under pressure. It's taught me a lot about accountability,
		problem solving, and getting things done in high stakes environments. But technology has
		always been where my curiosity lives.
	</p>

	<p>
		I've been building PCs since 2005, tinkering with home networks, and chasing down whatever
		problem needed solving, long before I had the vocabulary to describe what I was actually
		doing. I started formal IT coursework at Strayer University years ago, but life had other
		plans. Recently I picked it back up at El Camino Community College, and I'm on track to
		graduate with a 4.0 GPA in Cloud Computing and Information Systems in Fall 2026.
	</p>

	<p>
		In March 2026 I earned my AWS Certified Cloud Practitioner. My AWS Solutions Architect
		Associate exam is next.
	</p>

	<p>
		This site is part of that journey. It runs on AWS with S3, CloudFront, and ACM, deployed
		automatically through a CI/CD pipeline I built in GitHub Actions. The blog documents what
		I'm learning in real time, including a homelab I run on bare metal at home where I get
		hands on with the infrastructure concepts I'm studying.
	</p>

	<p>
		I'm looking for opportunities in cloud infrastructure, DevOps, or systems administration
		where I can keep growing and contribute from day one.
	</p>
</Layout>
